{"word":"μόρσιμος","slug":"μόρσιμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μόρσιμος</b></el> <el>(μόρσῐμος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μόρος'><el>μόρος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>appointed by fate, destined</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>fatalis</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>τὸ μόρσιμον</el> <i>destiny, doom</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>τὰ μόρσιμα</el> <b>Solon.</b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>fore-doomed to die</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}